com.travelbank.knit

Class KnitPresenter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.travelbank.knit.KnitPresenter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Contract type class generated by Knit.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MemoryEntity, MessageReceiver, NativeViewCallbacks, PresenterInterface

    public abstract class KnitPresenter<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PresenterInterface, MessageReceiver
    Presenter classes that are exposed to the developer by Knit. These need to be annotated with Presenter and a target view class to be registered with Knit. All KnitPresenters will have a InternalPresenter counterpart that is actually used by Knit framework to manage these. Views that are annotated with KnitView will automatically have their contracts created by Knit. Those contracts should be be given to this class. Contracts will be have all non-android, public & package-private methods of the view exposed.

      • request

        protected void request(java.lang.String data,
                       java.lang.Object... params)
        Request method with no async support. Use this if you want to go around the event based system. Discouraged! No async support. Runs on the thread it is called on via a ImmediateScheduler.
        Parameters:
        data - data the tag of the data that is requested.
        params - Extra parameters being passed to the ValueGenerator
